(173, 1, '2017-11-17 12:48:22', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<strong>Anxiety in Children</strong>\n\nAnxiety is a common condition where in a particular person experience nervousness, frustration and uncomfortable because of a certain event. It is associated with a pain in the chest and breathing problems. This is both encountered by adults and children. Once a child felt these, taking him to a medical expert is needed. In case it becomes worse, the anxious child may not want to show in public, unable to have friends and cannot participate in activities with other people. This will greatly affect his growth and relationships. This can also be the reason for a child to have low grades in school that may also affect his learning skills. The parents of a child with anxiety can also become anxious by keeping him out of stressful situations. If your child is among them, you should help in curing it in the soonest possible time.\n\n<strong>Symptoms of Anxiety to Children</strong>\n\ndizziness\nfatigue\ndifficult to sleep\ntantrums\nchoking\nbecome shaky\nblushing\naches in the head, stomach and back\ngoes to toilet more often\nholding parents tightly\nheart palpitation\nshyness\nrefuses schooling\n\nIn case these shows in your child you have to immediately request him to undergo a Beck Anxiety Inventory to know how serious his condition and as well as to be informed about the ways of overcoming it.\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\n<ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display: block; text-align: center;" data-ad-layout="in-article" data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626" data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\n<script>\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\n</script>\n\nWhat is Beck Anxiety Inventory?\n\nBeck Anxiety Inventory (BAI) is composed of a 21 questions which is used to determine the level of the anxiety disorder of a person. This is one way of knowing how to overcome anxiety. The inventory questions are referring to the person''s feeling in the recent months. Some anxiety indications are stinging sensation, numbness, sweating not because the temperature is hot and intense fear from bad situations. Previously, this inventory is not appropriate for children and to old people. But now there is a test which is especially designed for children and adolescents. Ages 7-18 can now take the beck anxiety inventory. This is simple and can be done within 5-10 minutes. The questions in the test are answered by marking a cross on the choices which depends on what the person feels. The assessments are about the feelings, emotional behaviors, thoughts and social impairments in children.\n\nBeck anxiety inventory test may help in diagnosing how serious is the anxiety symptoms. This test is widely used despite of the other tests which can also determine the stress level of an anxious person. It is different from many other tests because it separates the indications of anxiety and depression which are often regarded as the same.\n\nAnxiety Prevention for Children\n\nSupport him to challenge fundamental thoughts and beliefs.\nTeach him to accept negative outcomes.\nDemonstrate self relaxation techniques like breathing deeply.\nMotivate him to do some exercises and adequate sleep.\nHelp him to overcome the unpleasant situations.\nGive time to enjoy the things your child loves to do.\n\nIf you are very much concern with the condition of your child, you better know these information about anxiety in children, its symptoms, prevention and most importantly the beck anxiety inventory. In this way you can help him in dealing with anxiety and to start a normal life with the people around him.', 'Beck Anxiety Inventory for Anxious Children', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:48:22', '2017-11-17 12:48:22', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/?p=173', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(174, 1, '2017-11-17 12:49:49', '2017-11-17 12:49:49', '<strong>Anxiety in Children</strong>\r\n\r\nAnxiety is a common condition where in a particular person experience nervousness, frustration and uncomfortable because of a certain event. It is associated with a pain in the chest and breathing problems. This is both encountered by adults and children. Once a child felt these, taking him to a medical expert is needed. In case it becomes worse, the anxious child may not want to show in public, unable to have friends and cannot participate in activities with other people. This will greatly affect his growth and relationships. This can also be the reason for a child to have low grades in school that may also affect his learning skills. The parents of a child with anxiety can also become anxious by keeping him out of stressful situations. If your child is among them, you should help in curing it in the soonest possible time.\r\n\r\n<strong>Symptoms of Anxiety to Children</strong>\r\n\r\ndizziness\r\nfatigue\r\ndifficult to sleep\r\ntantrums\r\nchoking\r\nbecome shaky\r\nblushing\r\naches in the head, stomach and back\r\ngoes to toilet more often\r\nholding parents tightly\r\nheart palpitation\r\nshyness\r\nrefuses schooling\r\n\r\nIn case these shows in your child you have to immediately request him to undergo a Beck Anxiety Inventory to know how serious his condition and as well as to be informed about the ways of overcoming it. \r\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\r\n<ins class="adsbygoogle"\r\n     style="display:block; text-align:center;"\r\n     data-ad-layout="in-article"\r\n     data-ad-format="fluid"\r\n     data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626"\r\n     data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\nWhat is Beck Anxiety Inventory?\r\n\r\nBeck Anxiety Inventory (BAI) is composed of a 21 questions which is used to determine the level of the anxiety disorder of a person. This is one way of knowing how to overcome anxiety. The inventory questions are referring to the person''s feeling in the recent months. Some anxiety indications are stinging sensation, numbness, sweating not because the temperature is hot and intense fear from bad situations. Previously,  this inventory is not appropriate for children and to old people. But now there is a test which is especially designed for children and adolescents. Ages 7-18 can now take the beck anxiety inventory. This is simple and can be done within 5-10 minutes. The questions in the test are answered by marking a cross on the choices which depends on what the person feels. The assessments are about the feelings, emotional behaviors, thoughts and social impairments in children. \r\n\r\nBeck anxiety inventory test may help in diagnosing how serious is the anxiety symptoms. This test is widely used despite of the other tests which can also determine the stress level of an anxious person. It is different from many other tests because it separates the indications of anxiety and depression which are often regarded as the same.\r\n\r\nAnxiety Prevention for Children\r\n\r\nSupport him to challenge fundamental thoughts and beliefs.\r\nTeach him to accept negative outcomes.\r\nDemonstrate self relaxation techniques like breathing deeply.\r\nMotivate him to do some exercises and adequate sleep.\r\nHelp him to overcome the unpleasant situations.\r\nGive time to enjoy the things your child loves to do.\r\n\r\nIf you are very much concern with the condition of your child, you better know these information about anxiety in children, its symptoms, prevention and most importantly the beck anxiety inventory. In this way you can help him in dealing with anxiety and to start a normal life with the people around him.\r\n', 'Beck Anxiety Inventory for Anxious Children', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beck-anxiety-inventory-for-anxious-children', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:49:49', '2017-11-17 12:49:49', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/?p=174', 0, 'post', '', 0),
