 12:49:49', '', 174, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/174-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2017-11-17 12:50:50', '2017-11-17 12:50:50', 'Polarized sunglasses are protective eye wears that are made to shield the eyes from sun’s bright light. They reduce glare from reflective surfaces like water, glasses or snow with the help of special coatings put in them. In addition, they also have the capability to block eye damaging sun’s UV rays. They greatly help in avoiding bright light discomforts to the eye as they contain vertically polarized lens. \r\n\r\nWith all those benefits of using polarized sunglasses, there is no doubt that they are widely used for out of door activities. Parents would thank polarized sunglasses as kids can have the chance to experience very clear vision while lessening potential risks to their little precious eyes.\r\n\r\nChoosing the right sunglasses for kids is very crucial. When you want to protect your kid against any risk, these type of sunglasses are a great choice for them. In accordance to the American Optometric Association (AOA), kids are highly susceptible to acquiring eye damage from harmful ultraviolet rays as they have thinner lens where light is being filtered. It is said that almost 80% of a human lifetime is exposed to UV rays by the age of 20. Among eye problems that can be acquired due to overexposure to sun’s ultraviolet rays include macular degeneration, cataracts, pinguecula and pterygium, and photokeratitis. Other retinal damage can also occur from cumulative exposure to the sun.\r\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\r\n<ins class="adsbygoogle"\r\n     style="display:block; text-align:center;"\r\n     data-ad-layout="in-article"\r\n     data-ad-format="fluid"\r\n     data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626"\r\n     data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\nGetting young children and toddlers do not come easy as they can take them of the minute you put them When signs of trouble occur, keep in mind that you are building a healthy habit and this habit may take some time to form. on. It can be a hopeless battle but we should never give up as it will be worth the patience sooner or later. Yes, it is a struggle at first, but thinking how invaluable your kid’s eyes are, would never give you thoughts of giving up.\r\n\r\nGood thing is, kids polarized sunglasses are carefully designed to make kids look stylish and cool. They can be found in many different colors, designs and sizes to fit them properly. Kids love looking good and love colorful items. Letting them choose the design and color they want would be a good step to make. There are many brands you can find in the market so make sure to put proper attention to reading customer reviews before making a purchase.\r\n\r\nWith polarized kids sunglasses, headache and squirting can be avoided. Polarized sunglasses for kids and toddlers may come expensive than any other type of sunglasses but parents should keep in mind that quality comes first above anything else. Polarized kids sunglasses are designed with rubber material which is resistant to breakage. Also they contain polycarbonate lense that offers a hundred percent UV protection.\r\n', 'Why Polarized Sunglasses for Children Are Important?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-polarized-sunglasses-for-children-are-important', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:52:03', '2017-11-17 12:52:03', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/?p=177', 0, 'post', '', 0),
