(179, 1, '2017-11-17 12:50:50', '2017-11-17 12:50:50', 'Polarized sunglasses are protective eye wears that are made to shield the eyes from sun’s bright light. They reduce glare from reflective surfaces like water, glasses or snow with the help of special coatings put in them. In addition, they also have the capability to block eye damaging sun’s UV rays. They greatly help in avoiding bright light discomforts to the eye as they contain vertically polarized lens. \r\n\r\nWith all those benefits of using polarized sunglasses, there is no doubt that they are widely used for out of door activities. Parents would thank polarized sunglasses as kids can have the chance to experience very clear vision while lessening potential risks to their little precious eyes.\r\n\r\nChoosing the right sunglasses for kids is very crucial. When you want to protect your kid against any risk, these type of sunglasses are a great choice for them. In accordance to the American Optometric Association (AOA), kids are highly susceptible to acquiring eye damage from harmful ultraviolet rays as they have thinner lens where light is being filtered. It is said that almost 80% of a human lifetime is exposed to UV rays by the age of 20. Among eye problems that can be acquired due to overexposure to sun’s ultraviolet rays include macular degeneration, cataracts, pinguecula and pterygium, and photokeratitis. Other retinal damage can also occur from cumulative exposure to the sun.\r\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\r\n<ins class="adsbygoogle"\r\n     style="display:block; text-align:center;"\r\n     data-ad-layout="in-article"\r\n     data-ad-format="fluid"\r\n     data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626"\r\n     data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\nGetting young children and toddlers do not come easy as they can take them of the minute you put them When signs of trouble occur, keep in mind that you are building a healthy habit and this habit may take some time to form. on. It can be a hopeless battle but we should never give up as it will be worth the patience sooner or later. Yes, it is a struggle at first, but thinking how invaluable your kid’s eyes are, would never give you thoughts of giving up.\r\n\r\nGood thing is, kids polarized sunglasses are carefully designed to make kids look stylish and cool. They can be found in many different colors, designs and sizes to fit them properly. Kids love looking good and love colorful items. Letting them choose the design and color they want would be a good step to make. There are many brands you can find in the market so make sure to put proper attention to reading customer reviews before making a purchase.\r\n\r\nWith polarized kids sunglasses, headache and squirting can be avoided. Polarized sunglasses for kids and toddlers may come expensive than any other type of sunglasses but parents should keep in mind that quality comes first above anything else. Polarized kids sunglasses are designed with rubber material which is resistant to breakage. Also they contain polycarbonate lense that offers a hundred percent UV protection.\r\n', 'Why Polarized Sunglasses for Children Are Important?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '177-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:50:50', '2017-11-17 12:50:50', '', 177, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/177-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(180, 1, '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '<span style="font-weight: 400;">A 27-year-old entrepreneur Roger Jin said that it was his dream to build his own business since he was a kid. He believes that he can only find his success in entrepreneurship.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In order to achieve this faster, Jin took a double load in college and graduated in two and half years. His first business venture is an app called "Bridge". It is an app and website that connects people with the same interests in nearby areas. Unfortunately, Bridge did not work.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">He thought his second business idea while he was in a grocery store in China. He bought a Choco Pie, which is practically a chocolate-coated marshmallow snack, and thought that it is a shame how people outside Asia can''t try these snacks. That''s how his second business was born.</span>\r\n\r\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\r\n<ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display: block; text-align: center;" data-ad-layout="in-article" data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626" data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jin founded "Treats" which is a snack subscription service in the next three months. He searched for whose wholesale distributors, a warehouse where he can sort and ship packages and of course a website.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">For those who are not familiar with snack subscription services, here is the full explanation. A subscription box is basically a recurring delivery of niche products. But why subscription boxes are effective? The primary reason is because this business model provides a steady and predictable revenue stream. With the low cost of goods, ease of inventory management and manufacturers may also pay for category exclusivity and distribution. It is so easy to predict that quality subscription boxes that offers great products at affordable price are here to stay.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because of this Jin decided to create his own subscription box. He started it all in his living room using his $5000 savings. He received his first orders through his website late July 2015.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jin recounted the first six months of Treats and described it as a constant fight for survival. He took a lot of risks just to keep his company afloat while it is growing. He racked up thousands of debts on his credit card, and from different loans.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">He first advertised it on his high school''s Facebook Group, got his first customer and by December 2015, he started using branded blue Treats boxes. This is according to Jin what led to a big business growth.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Jin, it is in 2016 when Treats'' revenues hit seven figures. He currently employed 4 full-time employees and two part-time employees. Additionally, he also sub-contracts out the assembly of boxes and inventory management to Good Source, which is a revenue arm for Goodwill.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jin also added that aside from his goal of making Treats successful, he also saving money that he can use to start his next business, in this way he doesn''t have to rely on an outside capital.</span>', 'Is It Possible To Earn 7 Figures in 18 Months Working From Home? This 27-Year-Old Guy Did It!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'is-it-possible-to-earn-7-figures-in-18-months-working-from-home-this-27-year-old-guy-did-it', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/?p=180', 0, 'post', '', 0),
