exclusivity and distribution. It is so easy to predict that quality subscription boxes that offers great products at affordable price are here to stay.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Because of this Jin decided to create his own subscription box. He started it all in his living room using his $5000 savings. He received his first orders through his website late July 2015.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jin recounted the first six months of Treats and described it as a constant fight for survival. He took a lot of risks just to keep his company afloat while it is growing. He racked up thousands of debts on his credit card, and from different loans.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">He first advertised it on his high school''s Facebook Group, got his first customer and by December 2015, he started using branded blue Treats boxes. This is according to Jin what led to a big business growth.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to Jin, it is in 2016 when Treats'' revenues hit seven figures. He currently employed 4 full-time employees and two part-time employees. Additionally, he also sub-contracts out the assembly of boxes and inventory management to Good Source, which is a revenue arm for Goodwill.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Jin also added that aside from his goal of making Treats successful, he also saving money that he can use to start his next business, in this way he doesn''t have to rely on an outside capital.</span>', 'Is It Possible To Earn 7 Figures in 18 Months Working From Home? This 27-Year-Old Guy Did It!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '180-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '2017-11-17 12:51:41', '', 180, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/180-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `tns_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(183, 1, '2017-11-17 12:53:38', '2017-11-17 12:53:38', 'A new entrepreneur who chose to be called as "Jack" revealed that he decided to take the risk and sent $70,000 to a factory in Shenzhen, China, hoping that his money will not vanish.\r\n\r\nFortunately, after several weeks of waiting, 15,000 plastic toy cubes arrived. The toy has clickers and joysticks on each side and was specifically created for people who can''t keep still or often fidgets. His team was relieved and excited about the chance to make $345,000 in just a couple of months.\r\n<script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>\r\n<ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display: block; text-align: center;" data-ad-layout="in-article" data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-5184246098863626" data-ad-slot="4822388059"></ins>\r\n<script>\r\n     (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n</script>\r\n\r\nTaking chance in capitalizing on a different successful product from crowdfunding sites is scary. The staff of Stress Cube knows, however, they also believe that the rewards from it are tremendous.\r\n\r\nHow did it start? Jack apparently started with inflatable chairs.\r\n\r\nJack graduated from a college in Canada and after he worked on behalf of a social app hoping that one day he will eventually earn a billion-dollar valuation.\r\n\r\nBut he got bored with it and one day he realized what he wants, and that is to have an own company that sells various products.\r\n\r\nAt this time, he came across a startup that he thought will do well faster compare to others. He read about an Indiegogo campaign about inflatable lounge chairs made of parachute materials that made $18,500 in 12 hours in March.\r\n\r\nBecause of the popularity of Indiegogo, Jack researched about these chairs and realize that the idea was not unique. The only thing about it is that it gained attention through a crowdfunding campaign.\r\n\r\nAfter thinking about it, Jack decided to manufacture his own inflatable chair knockoff. A researched in Alibaba shows that a lot of manufacturer in China provide product samples. After organizing everything and going back and forth, Jack has successfully produced his own product, he named it The Cozy Bag.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nJack, together with his partner launched their company with just $5,000. They purchased 250 inflatable chairs, a secure domain name, and several Square credit card, readers. The following weeks, they spent it on selling chairs at fairs and concerts. At the same time, they started to build brand awareness on Instagram and Facebook.\r\n\r\nTheir sales increased so is their advertising expenses, which is necessary because of their several competitors.\r\n\r\nNearing their $100,000 mark, and as Jack looks for a new viral product, Google Trends alerted him about the Kickstarter''s top 10 most funded projects in history and there it was included, The Fidget Cube.\r\n\r\n<center></center>The Fidget Cube was designed to help anxious people to relax, each side of the cube has different clickers or joysticks. The campaign for it on Kickstarter reached $15,000 in less than 24 hours and almost $6.5 million in total.\r\n\r\nHowever, its popularity causes some manufacturing issues and delivery delays. This is when Jack and his partner decided to convert their Wordpress site and launch their own Stress Cube.\r\n\r\nThey ordered 1,000 cubes at $3.65 per piece and planned to sell them at $19.99 each. They also decided to use an automated software, FollowLiker that build brand awareness faster. His one Instagram ad generates $30,000 in sales.\r\n\r\nThey sold 100 fidget cubes in the following week. It also reached 800 a day on their pick. Which prompt them to hire contractors that help them in shipments and they also got a bigger office space.\r\n\r\nWhen their inventory diminished, they decided to order 15,000 stress cubes which cost them $70,000 to an unknown lady in China that they only met on Skype without any insurance that it will arrive.\r\n\r\nLuckily, the cubes arrived. However, their problems do not end there because they are now facing another worry. A patent issue arose and it can shut down their business that raised them almost $350,000 in just a couple of months. Aside from this, they can also face a lawsuit from the Fidget Cube''s parent company.\r\n\r\nAccording to Mark McLachlan, co-founder of Fidget Cube''s parent company Antsy Labs, the patent is still pending. He also shared his view about the knockoffs. He said that he is not excessively worried about the competition, and he believes that what matters most is the quality of the product.\r\n\r\nThis is what really concerns Jack, the patents. He said that he was checking for new updates every other day. Although it not an issue for him to turn and start again because he believed that the world is full of products. He does not specifically need to sell a particular product, he just wants to sell something that people likes. Also, his goal for the next 5 years is to have 10 product lines.\r\n\r\nLastly, he said that common aim of entrepreneurs to be profitable in the span of 18 months is not really relevant nowadays. Because like him, anyone can be profitable within 4 days.', 'How This 24-Year-Old Made $345,000 in 2 Months', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-this-24-year-old-made-345000-in-2-months', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:53:38', '2017-11-17 12:53:38', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/?p=183', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(184, 1, '2017-11-17 12:52:50', '2017-11-17 12:52:50', '', 'product', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'product', '', '', '2017-11-17 12:52:50', '2017-11-17 12:52:50', '', 183, 'http://127.0.0.1/trstn/trendnstuff/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/product.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
